<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="199" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,903,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1300,1325]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[328,494,1300,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Microlia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amici" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[328,494,1300,1325]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Microlia amici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[501,590,1300,1325]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[501,590,1300,1325]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[738,872,1300,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Microlia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meticola">
<emphasis box="[738,872,1300,1325]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">M. meticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by abdominal segments darker, mesotarsus with 
<number box="[1422,1436,1300,1325]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="5.0">5</number>
segments, tergum VII of male without tubercles, tergum VIII of male emarginated in posterior margin. In addition 
<taxonomicName box="[151,252,1373,1396]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Microlia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amici" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,252,1373,1396]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">M. amici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[262,353,1372,1397]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[262,353,1372,1397]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[697,794,1372,1397]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Microlia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[697,794,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Microlia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of median lobe, mainly the apical process (
<figureCitation box="[159,286,1407,1432]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1788,1811]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,205,1755]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[183,1403,193,1768]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Male, details of Microlia amici sp. nov. Paratype. 8. tergum III, dorsal view, setae removed; 9. tergum VII, dorsal view, setae removed; 10. tergum VIII, dorsal view; 11. sternum VIII, ventral view; 12. median lobe, ventral view; 13. median lobe, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.125 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270838/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Figs 
<number box="[215,286,1407,1432]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="12.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="12.0">
12 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[243,257,1407,1432]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">–</emphasis>
13
</number>
</figureCitation>
) and spermatheca forming a sinuously in shape, with female accessory sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[1185,1269,1407,1432]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1008,1031]" captionTargetBox="[191,1389,195,979]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[191,1396,193,987]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Female, Details of Microlia amici sp. nov. Paratype. 14. tergum VIII, dorsal view; 15. sternum VIII, ventral view; 16. spermatheca. Scale bars = 0.125 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270839/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[1238,1269,1407,1432]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,903,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,408,1444,1469]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Decription. Male.</emphasis>
Maximum body length: 
<quantity box="[687,777,1444,1469]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
; maximum elytra width: 
<quantity box="[1059,1148,1444,1469]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
. Body broad; head, elytra and abdomen somewhat red-brown to dark-brown, always abdomen darker; pronotum and appendices uniformly light-brown, except antennal apex with articles 
<number box="[688,743,1516,1541]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="9.0" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="7.0">
7 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[701,715,1516,1541]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">–</emphasis>
11
</number>
or 
<number box="[779,834,1516,1541]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="9.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="8.0">
8 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[793,807,1516,1541]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">–</emphasis>
11
</number>
darker. Dorsal surface glossy; setigerous pores sparse and more densely on pronotum and elytra; pronotum with pubescence directed posteriorly in midline and lateroposteriad in lateral areas; elytra and abdomen with pubescence straight and direct posteriad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,903,2009]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,896]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="199" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Head as long as wide; eyes 
<number box="[513,527,1624,1648]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.0">2</number>
times as long as temples; infraorbital carina complete. Antennal articles 
<number box="[1352,1366,1624,1648]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number box="[1422,1436,1624,1648]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.0">2</number>
subequal in length; 
<number box="[387,401,1660,1684]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.0">2</number>
slightly longer than 
<number box="[654,670,1660,1684]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="3.0">3</number>
; articles 
<number box="[781,823,1660,1685]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">
4 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[795,809,1660,1685]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">–</emphasis>
5
</number>
subquadrate, articles 
<number box="[1083,1139,1660,1685]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="8.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="6.0">
6 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1097,1111,1660,1685]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">–</emphasis>
10
</number>
transverse and gradually increasing in width toward antennal apex; article 
<number box="[734,762,1696,1720]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="10.0">10</number>
twice as wide as long; article 
<number box="[1130,1157,1696,1720]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="11.0">11</number>
as long as article 
<number box="[1380,1436,1695,1720]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">
9 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1394,1408,1695,1720]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">–</emphasis>
10
</number>
combined; with two coeloconic sensilla. Labrum transverse, anterior margin with four shallow emarginations (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[168,1415,193,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[168,1418,193,1943]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 7. Details of Microlia amici sp. nov. paratype. 3. labrum, dorsal view; 4. mandibles, dorsal view; 5. right maxilla, dorsal view; 6. labium (6 a) and hypopharinx (6 b), ventral view; 7. mesometathorax, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.125 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270837/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,167,1768,1792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Mandibles broad and curved at apex (
<figureCitation box="[641,715,1767,1792]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[168,1415,193,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[168,1418,193,1943]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 7. Details of Microlia amici sp. nov. paratype. 3. labrum, dorsal view; 4. mandibles, dorsal view; 5. right maxilla, dorsal view; 6. labium (6 a) and hypopharinx (6 b), ventral view; 7. mesometathorax, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.125 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270837/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[698,715,1768,1792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
); right mandible with small medial tooth, directed anteriorly; Maxilla with galea extending slightly beyond apex of lacinia, galea narrower than lacinia (
<figureCitation box="[1187,1257,1804,1829]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[168,1415,193,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[168,1418,193,1943]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 7. Details of Microlia amici sp. nov. paratype. 3. labrum, dorsal view; 4. mandibles, dorsal view; 5. right maxilla, dorsal view; 6. labium (6 a) and hypopharinx (6 b), ventral view; 7. mesometathorax, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.125 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270837/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[1241,1257,1804,1829]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
); apical lobe of galea covered with innumerable fine and short setae; apical half of lacinia with row of spaced spines, and basal half covered with numerous long setae; maxillary palpus with 
<number box="[799,813,1876,1900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="4.0">4</number>
articles and pseudoarticle, 
<number box="[1119,1132,1876,1901]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.0">2</number>
nd slightly shorter than 
<number box="[1399,1411,1876,1901]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="3.0">3</number>
rd and 
<number box="[201,215,1911,1936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="4.0">4</number>
th about half length of preceeding. Labium with ligula split into two lobes (
<figureCitation box="[1098,1169,1911,1936]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[168,1415,193,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[168,1418,193,1943]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 7. Details of Microlia amici sp. nov. paratype. 3. labrum, dorsal view; 4. mandibles, dorsal view; 5. right maxilla, dorsal view; 6. labium (6 a) and hypopharinx (6 b), ventral view; 7. mesometathorax, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.125 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270837/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[1154,1169,1911,1936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
a); labial palpus with 
<number box="[1422,1436,1912,1936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="3.0">3</number>
articles and pseudoarticle. Hypopharyngeal lobes well developed (
<figureCitation box="[934,1007,1948,1973]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[168,1415,193,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[168,1418,193,1943]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 7. Details of Microlia amici sp. nov. paratype. 3. labrum, dorsal view; 4. mandibles, dorsal view; 5. right maxilla, dorsal view; 6. labium (6 a) and hypopharinx (6 b), ventral view; 7. mesometathorax, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.125 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270837/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number box="[992,1007,1948,1973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Mentum with protruding anterior angles; gular plate broad. Elytra slightly broader than pronotum; posterior outer corners slightly emarginated. 
<collectingCountry box="[1380,1436,1984,2009]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Hind</collectingCountry>
wings fully developed. Mesoventrite process about half length of mesocoxae, acute and rounded at apex, mesocoxae slightly separated, mesocoxal cavities margined posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[978,1049,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[168,1415,193,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[168,1418,193,1943]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 7. Details of Microlia amici sp. nov. paratype. 3. labrum, dorsal view; 4. mandibles, dorsal view; 5. right maxilla, dorsal view; 6. labium (6 a) and hypopharinx (6 b), ventral view; 7. mesometathorax, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.125 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270837/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">
Fig. 
<number box="[1033,1049,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
); metaventrite process almost not existent; isthmus about 
<number box="[416,430,224,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[440,452,224,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="3.0">3</number>
as long as mesoventrite process. Tarsal formula 
<number box="[997,1038,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">
4 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1011,1025,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">–</emphasis>
5
</number>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1038,1052,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">–</emphasis>
<number box="[1052,1068,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="5.0">5</number>
; tarsomere 
<number box="[1199,1213,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="5.0">5</number>
the longest, as long as 
<number box="[184,198,260,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="3.0">3</number>
and 
<number box="[257,271,260,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="4.0">4</number>
combined. Abdomen gradually narrowing apically; first three visible terga deeply impressed basally; tergum III at posterior margin without projection (
<figureCitation box="[729,799,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1788,1811]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,205,1755]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[183,1403,193,1768]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Male, details of Microlia amici sp. nov. Paratype. 8. tergum III, dorsal view, setae removed; 9. tergum VII, dorsal view, setae removed; 10. tergum VIII, dorsal view; 11. sternum VIII, ventral view; 12. median lobe, ventral view; 13. median lobe, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.125 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270838/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">
Fig. 
<number box="[784,799,296,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
); tergum VII the longest, devoid of projection (
<figureCitation box="[1351,1421,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1788,1811]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,205,1755]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[183,1403,193,1768]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Male, details of Microlia amici sp. nov. Paratype. 8. tergum III, dorsal view, setae removed; 9. tergum VII, dorsal view, setae removed; 10. tergum VIII, dorsal view; 11. sternum VIII, ventral view; 12. median lobe, ventral view; 13. median lobe, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.125 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270838/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">
Fig. 
<number box="[1405,1421,296,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
); tergum VIII with small tubercles on front of posterior margin and posterior margin emarginated (
<figureCitation box="[1241,1324,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1788,1811]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,205,1755]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[183,1403,193,1768]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Male, details of Microlia amici sp. nov. Paratype. 8. tergum III, dorsal view, setae removed; 9. tergum VII, dorsal view, setae removed; 10. tergum VIII, dorsal view; 11. sternum VIII, ventral view; 12. median lobe, ventral view; 13. median lobe, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.125 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270838/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">
Fig. 
<number box="[1293,1324,332,356]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
); sternum VIII with posterior margin projected on median as pointed triangular lobe, pointed at the apex, and series of bifurcate setae (
<figureCitation box="[331,414,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1788,1811]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,205,1755]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[183,1403,193,1768]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Male, details of Microlia amici sp. nov. Paratype. 8. tergum III, dorsal view, setae removed; 9. tergum VII, dorsal view, setae removed; 10. tergum VIII, dorsal view; 11. sternum VIII, ventral view; 12. median lobe, ventral view; 13. median lobe, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.125 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270838/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">
Fig. 
<number box="[385,414,404,428]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
); tergum IX separated by tergum X and with symmetrical ventral struts; sternum IX three times as long as wide and two conspicuous short setae at apex; tergum X slightly emarginated at apex, with four long setae on each side and very weakly pigmented on median of posterior margin. Median lobe of aedeagus as 
<figureCitation box="[151,299,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1788,1811]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,205,1755]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[183,1403,193,1768]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Male, details of Microlia amici sp. nov. Paratype. 8. tergum III, dorsal view, setae removed; 9. tergum VII, dorsal view, setae removed; 10. tergum VIII, dorsal view; 11. sternum VIII, ventral view; 12. median lobe, ventral view; 13. median lobe, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.125 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270838/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">
Figs. 
<number box="[213,299,512,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="12.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="12.0">12 – 13</number>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="199" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,548,573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">Female.</emphasis>
Similar to male, except tergum VIII without small tubercles in front of posterior margin and almost truncate at posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[478,562,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1008,1031]" captionTargetBox="[191,1389,195,979]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[191,1396,193,987]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Female, Details of Microlia amici sp. nov. Paratype. 14. tergum VIII, dorsal view; 15. sternum VIII, ventral view; 16. spermatheca. Scale bars = 0.125 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270839/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">
Fig. 
<number box="[531,562,584,608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
); sternum VIII with slightly posterior margin projected medially, not forming as pointed triangular lobe as male; without bifurcate setae (
<figureCitation box="[822,906,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1008,1031]" captionTargetBox="[191,1389,195,979]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[191,1396,193,987]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Female, Details of Microlia amici sp. nov. Paratype. 14. tergum VIII, dorsal view; 15. sternum VIII, ventral view; 16. spermatheca. Scale bars = 0.125 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270839/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">
Fig. 
<number box="[875,906,620,645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
); tergum IX without ventral struts; sternum IX as ovipositor consisting of pair of ventral sclerites, each 
<number box="[797,811,656,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="3.0">3</number>
times as long as wide; tergum X with three long setae each side; spermatheca forming a sinuously in shape, with accessory sclerite near at base of subspherical capsule (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1008,1031]" captionTargetBox="[191,1389,195,979]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[191,1396,193,987]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Female, Details of Microlia amici sp. nov. Paratype. 14. tergum VIII, dorsal view; 15. sternum VIII, ventral view; 16. spermatheca. Scale bars = 0.125 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270839/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,243,727,752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="199" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,896]" box="[199,1011,764,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,764,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">Distribution.</emphasis>
Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[467,535,764,789]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Paraná: Balsa Nova, Rio dos Papagaios).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,896]" box="[199,994,799,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,393,799,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">Biological notes.</emphasis>
The specimens were collected in 
<taxonomicName box="[773,896,800,824]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
flowers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="199" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,836,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name “ 
<taxonomicName box="[569,635,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Microlia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amici">amici</taxonomicName>
” is a Latin masculine noun in genitive, that mean “friend” and it is an allusion to the dear friend and entomologist Paschoal Coelho Grossi that collected the 
<typeStatus box="[1119,1221,871,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
